Package: dmrfit
Date: 2026-03-16
Type: Package
Title: Optimization Tools for Discrete Markov Random Fields
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Giuseppe",
             family = "Arena",
             role = c("aut", "cre"),
             email = "g.arena@uva.nl",
             comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-5204-3326")))
Description: A set of tools designed for estimating discrete Markov Random Fields via pseudolikelihood, for both Ising models (Ising, 1925, <doi:10.1007/BF02980577>) and Ordinal Markov Random Fields (Marsman, M., van den Bergh, D., and Haslbeck, J. M. B, 2025, <doi:10.1017/psy.2024.4>). Parameters are estimated through a trust region optimization algorithm, with robust standard error estimation. The package supports both full network estimation,  where all edges are included, and constrained network estimation, where only a specified subset of edges is considered. 
